✅ Conceptual Notes Before Solving:
        - Count Digits,
        - Reverse Number,
        - Sum of Digits,
        - check palindrome num etc. [in all these type of questions, u mostly need to use while loop]
        - for single digit like 1,2,3 / 10 always return 0 and so for palindrome use condition
          while(num != 0) bcoz at the end num wll become 0 and there loop will break

int a = 43;
int b = 10;

System.out.println(a / b); // 4  (quotient)
System.out.println(a % b); // 3  (remainder)

So
/ gives quotient
% gives remainer

Another example -
121 / 10 -> 12 [removed last digit]
12 / 10 -> 1 [removed last digit]
1/10 -> 0

121 % 10 - 1
12 % 10 - 2
1 % 10 - 1

and so if u print last digits then it will print - 1 then 2 and then 1



🔢 Basic Math Behind Number Operations:

🔸 Division by 10 (num / 10)

	Removes last digit from a number.
	e.g. 123 / 10 = 12
	✅ Use this to drop last digit

🔸 Modulo by 10 (num % 10)

	Gives last digit of a number.
	e.g. 123 % 10 = 3
	✅ Use this to get last digit


-----------------------------------------------

🔁 Looping Strategy for Digit Problems

1) First fetch the last digit by % that num with 10 and store it in new var

Now we got the last digit of num, we need to remove that last digit from that num and that
we can do with / operator i.e.

2) Then to remove last digit from num -> divide that num by 10 and assign it to same var


while (num > 0) {
    let lastDigit = num % 10;       // ✅ get last digit
    num = Math.floor(num / 10);     // ✅ remove last digit
}


------------------------------------------------------------------

⚠️ Edge cases to consider:

1. num = 0

    Your current loop won’t run at all (while(num > 0)), so count stays 0.
    But 0 has 1 digit, so you need a special case: if(num == 0) count = 1;


2. Negative numbers

    Right now, negatives are ignored because while(num > 0) won’t run.
    You can fix it by taking absolute value:
    num = Math.abs(num);


Corrected version (handles all integers):

        int num = -4335;
        int count = 0;

        if (num == 0) {
            count = 1;
        } else {
            num = Math.abs(num);
            while(num > 0){
                count++;
                num /= 10;
            }
        }

        System.out.println("No of digits are - " + count);

        👉 This will give correct digit counts for positive, negative, and zero.
